body:
This seems the better way to do it because it doesn't impose any runtime cost to attribute lookup. It makes all of the shared types that have a `__module__` attribute inherit from a metaclass that reports the module correctly.

Supercedes https://github.com/cython/cython/pull/6845; fixes https://github.com/cython/cython/issues/6841

comment_data.body: We probably don't need to do this twice but can merge the two `changed` variables to do it at the end.

The order should be:
* `module_state_clear` - most of the `ModuleNode` generated code for clear
* `module_state_clear_contexts` - utility code injected into the clear function
* `module_state_clear_end` - pretty much just `return 0; }`

So the types are put near the end as you suggest.

comment_data.body:
I don't think so. Mainly because `cython_function_or_method` needs to have a descriptor so an individual CyFunction can store its `__module__`. Which means that `type(cython_function_or_method)` also needs to implement it as a descriptor.

(Of course, one option would be just to put `__module__` in `cython_function_or_method`'s dict, rather than implement it as a descriptor. I didn't particularly like this option because it means always creating a dict for every cyfunction. But it might have been easier)

commit.message:
Fix `__module__` attribute of shared types with metaclass

This seems the better way to do it because it doesn't impose
any runtime cost to attribute lookup. It makes all of the
shared types that have a `__module__` attribute inherit from
a metaclass that reports the module correctly.

Simpify getting module name

It's always the same

Make non-pickleability of coroutines (and related types) explicit

It may not be strictly needed, but I think it's a good thing to
do. For coroutines it's tested in test_coroutines_pep492, but
generators and async generator aren't explicitly tested so could
become pickleable accidentally.

Just disable the test of 3.8 Limited API

I can't make it work, and I think it's part of a long list of
similar things that don't really work on 3.8

Refactor declaration, initialization and cleanup of shared types

By moving them into utility code rather than having a list of
shared types in "Naming"
Make tests more robust so we find out if __module__ is wrong
Actually skip tests on Limited API 3.8
